## GAP-001 — Substrate-native square root

| field | value |
|---|---|
| **primitive_needed** | Typed square-root primitive that emits `TypedResult[float]` with declared status (`sqrt_observed`, `sqrt_domain_refused`, `sqrt_indeterminate`) and finite-precision provenance. Required because sqrt is a load-bearing observation in V4's quadratic root primitive, alpha probe, log-log slope SE, and four-form battery. |
| **required_layer** | L1 (substrate primitive) |
| **current_state** | `not_present` |
| **affected_consumers** | `src/lloyd_v4/primitives/stratified_quadratic_roots.py:248` (`math.sqrt(discriminant)`); `src/lloyd_v4/primitives/typed_log_log_slope.py:177` (`math.sqrt(...)` in standard-error formula); `src/lloyd_v4/primitives/directional_alpha_probe.py:502, 569` (`math.sqrt` in propagated_window_error and SE); all four-form battery eval scripts (`schwarzschild_*.py`, `sr_*.py`, `pure_algebraic_*.py`, `cbrt_*.py`) which call `math.sqrt`. |
| **workarounds** | Direct `math.sqrt` call (named-math import). Substrate accepts the floating-point value as substrate-traceable because `math.sqrt` is correctly-rounded in IEEE 754 (BACL and Conjecture C audits already characterise this), but the call itself is named-mathematical content per Axiom 11. |
| **failure_mode** | **Mode 3** — parent layer incomplete. The substrate has not declared a sqrt primitive; the typed quadratic-root primitive cannot honestly compose against one. |
| **remediation** | Add `typed_sqrt(x: float) -> TypedSqrtResult` at L1 with status family `{sqrt_observed, sqrt_domain_refused, sqrt_nonfinite}`. The substrate-native implementation can call `math.sqrt` internally *during the construction phase* (the Axiom 11′ refinement path), provided the call is wrapped in a typed envelope, the constant `math.sqrt` is declared a transition target with provenance, and the consumer-visible API never exposes raw `math.sqrt`. Per SUBSTRATE_CONSTRUCTION §3.4 (Generalisation), this is the natural decomposition of the operation. |
| **capability_spread** | **HIGH.** Consumers: 3 substrate primitives + ~14 eval scripts. Closing this gap is the prerequisite for Axiom 11 → Axiom 11′ criterion 1 ("every constant currently forbidden by Axiom 11 has a substrate-native equivalent"). |

